## PHASE 9C — PLAN SCHEDULE SYSTEM

### The 60-Day No-Repeat MOAT

Every plan has 60 unique day schedules. No dish repeats in 60 days. This is a business-level commitment that requires:

1. A scheduling algorithm that validates no recipe appears twice in a 60-day window
2. Seasonal rotation (monsoon recipes in Jun-Sep, summer in Mar-May)
3. Variety across meal types within a day (no two similar proteins in B+L)

### Schedule Validation Rule

```typescript
function validateSchedule(slots: PlanScheduleSlot[]): ValidationResult {
  const bySlot = groupBy(slots, 'mealSlot')

  for (const [slot, slotSlots] of Object.entries(bySlot)) {
    const recipeIds = slotSlots.map(s => s.recipeId)
    const unique = new Set(recipeIds)
    if (unique.size !== recipeIds.length) {
      return { valid: false, error: `Duplicate recipe in ${slot} slot` }
    }
  }

  // Also check: no same main ingredient (chicken) on consecutive days
  // No same cuisine type 3 days in a row
  return { valid: true }
}
```

